5) BETWEEN , NOT BETWEEN 
*)BETWEEN
Definition
BETWEEN is used to find values that lie between two given values. It includes both the starting and ending values.

Syntax
SELECT column_name
FROM table_name
WHERE column_name BETWEEN value1 AND value2;

Example
SELECT *
FROM Employees
WHERE salary BETWEEN 40000 AND 70000;

-> This returns employees whose salary is 40000, 50000, 60000, or 70000.

*)NOT BETWEEN

It is used to find values outside the given range.

Syntax
SELECT column_name
FROM table_name
WHERE column_name NOT BETWEEN value1 AND value2;

Example
SELECT *
FROM Employees
WHERE age NOT BETWEEN 25 AND 35;

-> This returns employees whose age is less than 25 or greater than 35.

Important Points
-> BETWEEN includes both the starting and ending values.
-> It works with numbers, dates, and text.
-> It is the same as:
WHERE salary >= 40000 AND salary <= 70000


